<eesti>Ajutise t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse h&uuml;vitise maksmine </eesti>
<inglise>Payment of Benefit for Temporary Incapacity for Work </inglise>
<eesti>(14.06.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 57, 374) </eesti>
<inglise>(14.06.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 57, 374) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Ajutise t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse h&uuml;vitis </eesti>
<inglise>Benefit for temporary incapacity for work </inglise>
<eesti>(14.06.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 57, 374) </eesti>
<inglise>(14.06.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 57, 374) </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ajutise t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse h&uuml;vitis (edaspidi h&uuml;vitis) on rahaline kompensatsioon, mida haigekassa maksab kindlustatule t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuslehe alusel juhul, kui t&ouml;&ouml;vabastuse t&otilde;ttu j&auml;&auml;b saamata sotsiaalmaksuga maksustatav tulu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Benefit for temporary incapacity for work (hereinafter benefit) is financial compensation paid by the health insurance fund to an insured person on the basis of a certificate of incapacity for work if income subject to social tax is not received due to leave. </inglise>
<eesti>(14.06.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 57, 374) </eesti>
<inglise>(14.06.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 57, 374) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ravikindlustuse h&uuml;vitise liigid on: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The classes of health insurance benefits are: </inglise>
<eesti>1) haigush&uuml;vitis, mida makstakse haiguslehe alusel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) sickness benefit paid on the basis of a certificate for sick leave; </inglise>
<eesti>2) s&uuml;nnitush&uuml;vitis, mida makstakse s&uuml;nnituslehe alusel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) maternity benefit paid on the basis of a certificate for maternity leave; </inglise>
<eesti>3) hooldush&uuml;vitis, mida makstakse hoolduslehe alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>3) care allowance paid on the basis of a certificate for care leave. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.12.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.12.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetusleht </eesti>
<inglise>Certificate of incapacity for work </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetusleht on kindlustatu ajutist t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetust ja t&ouml;&ouml;vabastust t&otilde;endav, h&uuml;vitise m&auml;&auml;ramise ja maksmise aluseks v&auml;ljaantav dokument. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A certificate of incapacity for work is a document which certifies the temporary incapacity for work and leave of an insured person and which is issued as the basis for the grant and payment of a benefit. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuslehe liigid on: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The types of certificates of incapacity for work are: </inglise>
<eesti>1) haigusleht; </eesti>
<inglise>1) certificate for sick leave; </inglise>
<eesti>2) hooldusleht; </eesti>
<inglise>2) certificate for care leave; </inglise>
<eesti>3) s&uuml;nnitusleht. </eesti>
<inglise>3) certificate for maternity leave. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuslehe v&auml;ljaandmise korra ning t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuslehe vormid ja t&auml;itmise juhendi kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The procedure for the issue of certificates of incapacity for work and the standard format of certificates of incapacity for work and instructions for the completion thereof shall be established by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.12.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.12.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuslehe alusel h&uuml;vitise maksmise juhud </eesti>
<inglise>Cases of payment of benefit on basis of certificate of incapacity for work </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Haiguslehe alusel makstakse h&uuml;vitist j&auml;rgmistel ajutise t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse juhtudel: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A benefit shall be paid on the basis of a certificate for sick leave in the following cases of temporary incapacity for work: </inglise>
<eesti>1) haiguse v&otilde;i vigastuse korral; </eesti>
<inglise>1) illness or injury; </inglise>
<eesti>2) taastusravi korral; </eesti>
<inglise>2) medical rehabilitation; </inglise>
<eesti>3) haiglas proteesi paigaldamise korral; </eesti>
<inglise>3) application of a prosthesis in a hospital; </inglise>
<eesti>4) karantiini korral; </eesti>
<inglise>4) quarantine; </inglise>
<eesti>5) Eesti Vabariigi t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduse (RT 1992, 15/16, 241; 1993, 10, 150; RT I 1993, 26, 441; 1995, 14, 170; 16, 228; 1996, 3, 57; 40, 773; 45, 850; 49, 953; 1997, 5/6, 32; 1998, 111, 1829; 1999, 16, 276; 60, 616; 2000, 25, 144; 51, 327; 57, 370; 102, 669; 2001, 17, 78; 42, 233; 53, 311) paragrahvide 62 ja 63 alusel ajutiselt t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste kergendamise v&otilde;i ajutiselt teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le &uuml;leviimise korral ning avaliku teenistuse seaduse (RT I 1995, 16, 228; RT I 1999, 7, 112; 10, 155; 16, 271 ja 276; 2000, 25, 144 ja 145; 28, 167; 102, 672; 2001, 7, 17 ja 18; 17, 78; 42, 233; 47, 260) paragrahv 51 alusel teenistustingimuste ajutise kergendamise v&otilde;i ajutiselt teisele ametikohale &uuml;leviimise korral. </eesti>
<inglise>5) temporary easement of working conditions or temporary transfer to another position on the basis of Article 62 or 63 of the Republic of Estonia Employment Contracts Act (RT 1992, 15/16, 241; 1993, 10, 150; RT I 1993, 26, 441; 1995, 14, 170; 16, 228; 1996, 3, 57; 40, 773; 45, 850; 49, 953; 1997, 5/6, 32; 1998, 111, 1829; 1999, 16, 276; 60, 616; 2000, 25, 144; 51, 327; 57, 370; 102, 669; 2001, 17, 78; 42, 233; 53, 311), and temporary easement of conditions of service or temporary transfer to another position on the basis of Article 51 of the Public Service Act (RT I 1995, 16, 228; RT I 1999, 7, 112; 10, 155; 16, 271 ja 276; 2000, 25, 144 ja 145; 28, 167; 102, 672; 2001, 7, 17 ja 18; 17, 78; 42, 233; 47, 260). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) S&uuml;nnituslehe alusel makstakse h&uuml;vitist j&auml;rgmistel juhtudel: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A benefit shall be paid on the basis of a certificate for maternity leave in the following cases: </inglise>
<eesti>1) rasedus- ja s&uuml;nnituspuhkuse korral; </eesti>
<inglise>1) pregnancy and maternity leave; </inglise>
<eesti>2) (Kehtetu - 04.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 42, 233) </eesti>
<inglise>2) (Repealed - 04.04.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 42, 233) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Hoolduslehe alusel makstakse h&uuml;vitist j&auml;rgmistel juhtudel: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A benefit shall be paid on the basis of a certificate for care leave in the following cases: </inglise>
<eesti>1) haige perekonnaliikme kodus p&otilde;etamise korral; </eesti>
<inglise>1) nursing a family member who is ill at home; </inglise>
<eesti>2) alla 14-aastase haige lapse p&otilde;etamise korral; </eesti>
<inglise>2) nursing a child under 14 years of age who is ill; </inglise>
<eesti>3) alla 3-aastase lapse (alla 16-aastase lapsinvaliidi) hooldamise korral, kui last hooldav isik on haige v&otilde;i viibib haiglas seoses s&uuml;nnitusega; </eesti>
<inglise>3) caring for a child under 3 years of age (or a disabled child under 16 years of age) if the person caring for the child is ill or is in hospital due to childbirth; </inglise>
<eesti>(09.12.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.12.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </inglise>
<eesti>4) alla 4-aastase lapse lapsendaja puhkuse korral. </eesti>
<inglise>4) adoptive parents leave for an adoptive parent of a child under 4 year of age. </inglise>
<eesti>(04.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 42, 233) </eesti>
<inglise>(04.04.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 42, 233) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>H&uuml;vitise maksmise kestus </eesti>
<inglise>Duration of payment of benefit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kindlustatule makstakse h&uuml;vitist esmase haiguslehe vormistamise kalendrip&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast kalendrip&auml;evast: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A benefit shall be paid to an insured person from the calendar day following the calendar day on which an initial certificate for sick leave is prepared: </inglise>
<eesti>1) haiguse, vigastuse, taastusravi ja haiglas proteesi paigaldamise korral kuni haiguslehel m&auml;rgitud t&ouml;&ouml;vabastuse l&otilde;puni v&otilde;i p&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse kindlakstegemise p&auml;evani (kaasa arvatud), kuid &uuml;he haiguse korral mitte rohkem kui 182 kalendrip&auml;eva j&auml;rjest; tuberkuloosi haigestumise korral mitte rohkem kui 240 kalendrip&auml;eva j&auml;rjest. </eesti>
<inglise>1) in the case of illness, injury, medical rehabilitation or application of a prosthesis in a hospital, until the end of the leave indicated on the certificate for sick leave or until the day on which permanent incapacity for work is determined (inclusive), but for not more than 182 consecutive calendar days during one illness or, in the case of contraction of tuberculosis, for not more than 240 consecutive calendar days. </inglise>
<eesti>P&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse alguse p&auml;evaks loetakse p&uuml;sivalt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuks tunnistamise p&auml;ev; </eesti>
<inglise>The day on which permanent incapacity for work is declared is deemed to be the day on which permanent incapacity for work commences; </inglise>
<eesti>2) karantiini korral kuni haiguslehel m&auml;rgitud t&ouml;&ouml;vabastuse l&otilde;puni, kuid mitte rohkem kui seitsme kalendrip&auml;eva eest; </eesti>
<inglise>2) in the case of quarantine, until the end of the leave indicated on the certificate for sick leave but for not more than seven calendar days; </inglise>
<eesti>3) Eesti Vabariigi t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduse paragrahv 62 alusel ajutiselt t&ouml;&ouml;lt vabastamise korral kuni haiguslehel m&auml;rgitud t&ouml;&ouml;vabastuse l&otilde;puni, kuid mitte rohkem kui 60 kalendrip&auml;eva eest; </eesti>
<inglise>3) in the case of being released from work on the basis of Article 62 of the Republic of Estonia Employment Contracts Act, until the end of the leave indicated on the certificate for sick leave but for not more than sixty calendar days; </inglise>
<eesti>4) Eesti Vabariigi t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduse paragrahv 62 alusel ajutiselt t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste kergendamise v&otilde;i ajutiselt teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le &uuml;leviimise korral makstakse h&uuml;vitist palgavahe ulatuses kuni ajutiselt teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le &uuml;leviimise v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste kergendamise l&otilde;puni, kuid mitte rohkem kui 60 kalendrip&auml;eva eest; </eesti>
<inglise>4) in the case of temporary easement of working conditions or temporary transfer to another position on the basis of Article 62 of the Republic of Estonia Employment Contracts Act, in an amount equal to the difference in wages until the end of the temporary easement of working conditions or temporary transfer to another position but for not more than sixty calendar days; </inglise>
<eesti>5) Eesti Vabariigi t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduse paragrahv 63 v&otilde;i avaliku teenistuse seaduse paragrahv 51 alusel ajutiselt t&ouml;&ouml;lt vabastamise korral kuni haiguslehel m&auml;rgitud t&ouml;&ouml;vabastuse l&otilde;puni; </eesti>
<inglise>5) in the case of temporary release from work on the basis of Article 63 of the Republic of Estonia Employment Contracts Act or Article 51 of the Public Service Act, until the end of the leave indicated on the certificate for sick leave; </inglise>
<eesti>6) Eesti Vabariigi t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduse paragrahv 63 alusel ajutiselt t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste kergendamise v&otilde;i ajutiselt teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le &uuml;leviimise korral v&otilde;i avaliku teenistuse seaduse paragrahv 51 alusel ajutiselt teenistustingimuste kergendamise v&otilde;i ajutiselt teisele ametikohale &uuml;leviimise korral makstakse h&uuml;vitist palgavahe ulatuses kuni ajutiselt teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le &uuml;leviimise v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste kergendamise l&otilde;puni. </eesti>
<inglise>6) in the case of temporary easement of working conditions or temporary transfer to another position on the basis of Article 63 of the Republic of Estonia Employment Contracts Act or in the case of temporary easement of conditions of service or temporary transfer to another position on the basis of Article 51 of the Public Service Act, in an amount equal to the difference in wages until the end of the temporary transfer to another position or temporary easement of working conditions. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 1 nimetatud juhtudel suunab raviarst kindlustatu hiljemalt 120. haigusp&auml;evaks, tuberkuloosi haigestumise korral hiljemalt 178. haigusp&auml;evaks arstliku ekspertiisi komisjoni ravi j&auml;tkamise otsuse saamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the cases specified in clause (1) 1) of this section, the attending physician shall, not later than by the 120th day of sick leave or, in the case of contraction of tuberculosis, not later than by the 178th day of sick leave, refer the insured person to a medical assessment committee for a decision concerning the continuation of treatment. </inglise>
<eesti>Arstliku ekspertiisi komisjoni otsusega on raviarstil &otilde;igus pikendada t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuslehte kuni 62 kalendrip&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise>If the medical assessment committee decides to continue the treatment, the attending physician has the right to extend the certificate of incapacity for work by up to sixty-two calendar days. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kindlustatule makstakse h&uuml;vitist s&uuml;nnituslehe vormistamise p&auml;evast (kaasa arvatud): </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A benefit shall be paid to an insured person from the day on which the certificate for maternity leave is prepared (inclusive): </inglise>
<eesti>1) rasedus- ja s&uuml;nnituspuhkuse korral mitte rohkem kui 126 kalendrip&auml;eva eest. Mitmikute s&uuml;nni v&otilde;i t&uuml;sistustega s&uuml;nnituse korral mitte rohkem kui 140 kalendrip&auml;eva eest; </eesti>
<inglise>1) in the case of pregnancy and maternity leave, for not more than 126 calendar days, or in the case of a multiple birth or a delivery with complications, for not more than 140 calendar days; </inglise>
<eesti>2) (Kehtetu - 04.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 42, 233) </eesti>
<inglise>2) (Repealed - 04.04.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 42, 233) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kindlustatule makstakse h&uuml;vitist hoolduslehe vormistamise p&auml;evast (kaasa arvatud) kuni hoolduslehel m&auml;rgitud t&ouml;&ouml;vabastuse l&otilde;puni: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A benefit shall be paid to an insured person from the day on which the certificate for care leave is prepared (inclusive) until the end of the leave indicated on the certificate for care leave: </inglise>
<eesti>1) haige perekonnaliikme (v&auml;lja arvatud alla 14-aastane laps) kodus p&otilde;etamise korral, kuid mitte rohkem kui seitsme kalendrip&auml;eva eest; </eesti>
<inglise>1) in the case of nursing a family member (except a child under 14 years of age) who is ill at home, but for not more than seven calendar days; </inglise>
<eesti>2) alla 3-aastase lapse (alla 16-aastase lapsinvaliidi) hooldamise korral, kui last hooldav isik on haige v&otilde;i viibib haiglas seoses s&uuml;nnitusega, kuid mitte rohkem kui 14 kalendrip&auml;eva eest; </eesti>
<inglise>2) in the case of caring for a child under 3 years of age (or a disabled child under 16 years of age) if the person caring for the child is ill or is in hospital due to childbirth, but for not more than fourteen calendar days; </inglise>
<eesti>3) alla 14-aastase haige lapse p&otilde;etamise korral, kuid mitte rohkem kui 14 kalendrip&auml;eva eest; </eesti>
<inglise>3) in the case of nursing a child under 14 years of age who is ill, but for not more than fourteen calendar days; </inglise>
<eesti>4) alla 4-aastase lapse lapsendaja puhkuse korral hoolduslehe alusel 70 kalendrip&auml;eva eest, arvates lapsendamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>4) in the case of adoptive parents leave for an adoptive parent of a child under 4 years of age on the basis of a certificate for care leave, for seventy calendar days as of the date of adoption. </inglise>
<eesti>(04.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 42, 233) </eesti>
<inglise>(04.04.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 42, 233) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kindlustatu haigestumise v&otilde;i vigastuse korral v&auml;lisriigis m&auml;&auml;rab ja maksab haigekassa sotsiaalministri poolt kehtestatud juhtudel h&uuml;vitist v&auml;lisriigis arsti poolt v&auml;ljaantud haigestumist t&otilde;endava dokumendi alusel k&auml;esolevas seaduses etten&auml;htud tingimustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) In the case of illness of or injury to an insured person in a foreign state, the health insurance fund shall grant and pay a benefit in the cases established by the Minister of Social Affairs on the basis of a document certifying illness or injury issued by a doctor in the foreign state under the conditions and pursuant to the procedure prescribed by this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.12.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.12.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>H&uuml;vitise m&auml;&auml;ramine ja maksmine </eesti>
<inglise>Grant and payment of benefit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 6 nimetatud h&uuml;vitise m&auml;&auml;rab ja maksab kindlustatule haigekassa. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A benefit specified in Article 6 of this Act shall be granted and paid to an insured person by the health insurance fund. </inglise>
<eesti>(14.06.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 57, 374) </eesti>
<inglise>(14.06.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 57, 374) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) H&uuml;vitis m&auml;&auml;ratakse ja makstakse, kui sotsiaalmaksumaksja on esitanud haigekassale kindlustatu t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuslehe koos h&uuml;vitise m&auml;&auml;ramiseks ja maksmiseks vajalike t&otilde;enditega hiljemalt 180. kalendrip&auml;eval, arvates t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuslehel m&auml;rgitud t&ouml;&ouml;leasumise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A benefit shall be granted and paid not later than by the 180th calendar day after the date of commencing work indicated on the certificate of incapacity for work if the payer of social tax has submitted the certificate of incapacity for work of the insured person to the health insurance fund together with the documentation necessary for the grant and payment of the benefit. </inglise>
<eesti>Kokkuleppel t&ouml;&ouml;andjaga v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuslehe ja vajalikud t&otilde;endid haigekassale esitada ka kindlustatu. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon agreement with the employer, the certificate of incapacity for work and the necessary documentation may be submitted to the health insurance fund also by the insured person. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.12.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.12.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) H&uuml;vitis makstakse v&auml;lja vastavalt h&uuml;vitise saaja soovile tema pangaarvele v&otilde;i posti teel h&uuml;vitise maksja kulul 30 kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul, arvates t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuslehe ja n&otilde;uetekohaselt vormistatud t&otilde;endite haigekassale esitamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A benefit shall be paid into the bank account of the recipient of the benefit or by post at the expense of the payer of the benefit, as requested by the recipient, within thirty calendar days after the date on which the certificate of incapacity for work and documentation prepared as required are submitted to the health insurance fund. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.12.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.12.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) H&uuml;vitise maksmisega viivitamisel &uuml;le k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 3. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud t&auml;htaja maksab haigekassa kindlustatule iga viivitatud p&auml;eva eest viivist 0,5% maksmisele kuuluvast summast. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If payment of a benefit is delayed until after the term specified in subsection (3) of this section, the health insurance fund shall pay the insured person a fine for delay of 0.5 per cent of the amount payable for each day payment is delayed. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.12.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.12.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) H&uuml;vitise maksmisel &uuml;mardatakse 50 senti ja &uuml;le selle &uuml;he kroonini, summat alla 50 sendi ei arvestata. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon payment of a benefit, amounts of 50 sents and more shall be rounded to one kroon (EEK), and amounts of less than 50 sents shall not be taken into account. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.12.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.12.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </inglise>
<eesti>(6) H&uuml;vitise m&auml;&auml;ramise ja maksmise korra ning h&uuml;vitise m&auml;&auml;ramiseks ja maksmiseks vajalike t&otilde;endite vormid, samuti h&uuml;vitise arvutamise juhendi kehtestab sotsiaalminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The procedure for the grant and payment of a benefit, the standard format of the documentation necessary for the grant and payment of a benefit, and the instructions for the calculation of a benefit shall be established by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.12.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.12.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Kindlustatu t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuslehel m&auml;rgitud t&ouml;&ouml;st vabastamise ajal t&ouml;&ouml;le lubamise keeld </eesti>
<inglise>Prohibition of permission for insured person to work during leave indicated on certificate of incapacity for work </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on keelatud lubada kindlustatut t&ouml;&ouml;le t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuslehel m&auml;rgitud t&ouml;&ouml;st vabastamise ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>An employer is prohibited from permitting an insured person to work during the leave indicated on the certificate of incapacity for work. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.12.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.12.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10 (2). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10 (2). </inglise>
<eesti>H&uuml;vitise arvutamise alus </eesti>
<inglise>Basis for calculation of benefit </inglise>
<eesti>H&uuml;vitise arvutamise aluseks on kindlustatu sotsiaalmaksuga maksustatud tulu j&auml;rgi arvutatud &uuml;he kalendrip&auml;eva keskmine tulu. </eesti>
<inglise>The basis for the calculation of a benefit is average income per calendar day calculated from the income of the insured person which is subject to social tax. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.12.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.12.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10 (3). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10 (3). </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;he kalendrip&auml;eva keskmise tulu arvutamise alused </eesti>
<inglise>Bases for calculation of average income per calendar day </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Uuml;he kalendrip&auml;eva keskmine tulu kindlustatul, kelle eest maksab sotsiaalmaksu t&ouml;&ouml;andja, arvutatakse t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuslehel m&auml;rgitud t&ouml;&ouml;vabastuse algusp&auml;eva kalendrikuule eelnenud kuuel kalendrikuul t&ouml;&ouml;andjate poolt kindlustatule arvestatud sotsiaalmaksuga maksustatud tulu liitmisel ning saadud summa jagamisel selle perioodi (kuue kuu) kalendrip&auml;evade arvuga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The average income per calendar day of an insured person for whom social tax is paid by an employer shall be calculated by adding together the income subject to social tax calculated for the insured person by employers during the six calendar months preceding the calendar month of the day on which the leave indicated on the certificate of incapacity to work commenced and dividing the result by the number of calendar days during the period (six months). </inglise>
<eesti>(09.12.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.12.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike alusel arvutatud &uuml;he kalendrip&auml;eva keskmine tulu on v&auml;iksem summast, mis saadakse t&ouml;&ouml;vabastuse algusp&auml;eval kehtiva Vabariigi Valitsuse poolt kehtestatud kuupalga alamm&auml;&auml;ra (edaspidi kuupalga alamm&auml;&auml;r) jagamisel 30-ga, arvutatakse &uuml;he kalendrip&auml;eva keskmine tulu kuupalga alamm&auml;&auml;ra jagamisel 30-ga, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 6 nimetatud juhul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the average income per calendar day calculated on the basis of subsection (1) of this section is less than the result of dividing the minimum monthly wage established by the Government of the Republic (hereinafter minimum monthly wage) valid on the day on which leave commences by thirty, the average income per calendar day shall be calculated by dividing the minimum monthly wage by thirty. </inglise>
<eesti>(18.02.99 j&otilde;ust.01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 29, 397) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.02.99 entered into force 01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 29, 397) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Uuml;he kalendrip&auml;eva keskmine tulu kindlustatul, kes tegeleb f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjana, arvutatakse perioodil 1. juuli kuni j&auml;rgmise kalendriaasta 30. juuni alanud t&ouml;&ouml;vabastuse korral nimetatud perioodile eelnenud kalendriaastal (1. jaanuar kuni 31. detsember) f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjana saadud sotsiaalmaksuga maksustatud tulu jagamisel 365 kalendrip&auml;evaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The average income per calendar day of an insured person who is operating as a sole proprietor shall be calculated, in the case of leave commencing during the period from 1 July to 30 June of the following calendar year, by dividing the income which is subject to social tax and received during the calendar year (1 January to 31 December) prior to the specified period from operations as a sole proprietor by 365 calendar days. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.12.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.12.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui kindlustatule ei arvestatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud perioodil sotsiaalmaksuga maksustatud tulu, arvutatakse &uuml;he kalendrip&auml;eva keskmine tulu t&ouml;&ouml;vabastuse algusp&auml;eval kehtiva kuupalga alamm&auml;&auml;ra jagamisel 30-ga, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 6. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud juhul. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If income subject to social tax is not calculated for an insured person during the period specified in subsection (1) of this section, the average income per calendar day shall be calculated by dividing the minimum monthly wage valid on the day on which the leave commences by thirty, except in the case specified in subsection (6) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(24.10.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 84, 536) </eesti>
<inglise>(24.10.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 84, 536) </inglise>
<eesti>(4 (1)) Kui kindlustatu ei saanud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 3. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud kalendriaastal f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjana sotsiaalmaksuga maksustatud tulu, arvutatakse &uuml;he kalendrip&auml;eva keskmine tulu sotsiaalmaksuseaduse &sect; 6 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud ja t&ouml;&ouml;vabastuse algusp&auml;eval kehtinud kuum&auml;&auml;ra jagamisel 30-ga, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 5. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud juhul. </eesti>
<inglise>(4 (1)) If an insured person does not, as a sole proprietor, receive income subject to social tax during the calendar year specified in subsection (3) of this section, the average income per calendar day shall be calculated by dividing the monthly rate which is provided in subsection 6 (2) of the Social Tax Act and which is valid on the day on which the leave commences by thirty, except in the case specified in subsection (5) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(24.10.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 84, 536; 13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 675) </eesti>
<inglise>(24.10.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 84, 536; 13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 675) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) F&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjale, kes koosk&otilde;las sotsiaalmaksuseaduse &sect; 9 l&otilde;ike 3 punktiga 1 v&otilde;i l&otilde;ikega 4 ei ole maksnud sotsiaalmaksu avansilisi makseid, h&uuml;vitist ei maksta. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A benefit shall not be paid to a sole proprietor who, in accordance with clause 9 (3) 1) of the Social Tax Act, has not made advance payments of social tax. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.12.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 675) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.12.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 102, 675) </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kui kindlustatu p&otilde;hipalk kuus on t&ouml;&ouml;vabastuse algusp&auml;eval v&auml;iksem kuupalga alamm&auml;&auml;rast, arvutatakse &uuml;he kalendrip&auml;eva keskmine tulu p&otilde;hipalga jagamisel 30-ga. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) If the basic monthly wage of an insured person on the day on which leave commences is less than the minimum monthly wage, the average income per calendar day shall be calculated by dividing the basic wage by thirty. </inglise>
<eesti>(18.02.99 j&otilde;ust.01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 29, 397) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.02.99 entered into force 01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 29, 397) </inglise>
<eesti>(7) &Uuml;he kalendrip&auml;eva keskmise tulu arvutamisel ei v&otilde;eta arvesse kalendrip&auml;evi, mil kindlustatu oli t&ouml;&ouml;lt vabastatud t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuslehe alusel, samuti k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 10 (5) 4. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud t&ouml;&ouml;lt puudutud p&auml;evi ning Eesti Vabariigi puhkuseseaduse (RT 1992, 37, 481; 1993, 10, 150; RT I 1994, 84, 1474; 1995, 16, 228; 1997, 74, 1229; 93, 1560) paragrahv 9 2. l&otilde;ike punktide 1 ja 2 alusel &uuml;le 28 kalendrip&auml;eva antud puhkuse ja paragrahv 31 alusel antud t&auml;iendava lapsepuhkuse p&auml;evi. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Upon the calculation of average income per calendar day, calendar days on which the insured person was on leave on the basis of a certificate of incapacity for work, days of absence from work specified in subsection 10 (5) (4) of this Act, days of holiday of more than 28 calendar days granted on the basis of clauses 9 (2) 1) or 2) of the Republic of Estonia Holidays Act (RT 1992, 37, 481; 1993, 10, 150; RT I, 1994, 84, 1474; 1995, 16, 228; 1997, 74, 1229; 93, 1560) and days of additional child care leave granted on the basis of Article 31 of the Republic of Estonia Holidays Act shall not be taken into account. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.12.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.12.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10 (4). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10 (4). </inglise>
<eesti>H&uuml;vitise m&auml;&auml;r </eesti>
<inglise>Rate of benefit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Haigekassa maksab kindlustatule h&uuml;vitist &uuml;he kalendrip&auml;eva kohta &uuml;he kalendrip&auml;eva keskmisest tulust j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The health insurance fund shall pay a benefit to an insured person per calendar day as a percentage of his or her average income per calendar day, as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) haiglaravi ja statsionaarse taastusravi, alla 14-aastase haige lapse haiglas v&otilde;i statsionaarses taastusraviasutuses p&otilde;etamise korral - 60%; </eesti>
<inglise>1) in the case of hospitalisation, in-patient medical rehabilitation, or nursing a child under 14 years of age who is ill in a hospital or in-patient medical rehabilitation institution - 60%; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ambulatoorse ravi, ambulatoorse taastusravi, p&auml;evase statsionaarse ravi, &uuml;le 14-aastase haige perekonnaliikme kodus p&otilde;etamise ja alla 3-aastase lapse (alla 16-aastase lapsinvaliidi) hooldamise korral, kui last hooldav isik on haige v&otilde;i haiglas seoses s&uuml;nnitusega - 80%; </eesti>
<inglise>2) in the case of out-patient treatment, out-patient medical rehabilitation, day care surgery and procedures, nursing a family member over 14 years of age who is ill at home, or caring for a child under 3 years of age (or a disabled child under 16 years of age) if the person caring for the child is ill or is in hospital due to childbirth - 80%; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetuse, riigi v&otilde;i &uuml;hiskonna huvide kaitsel ja kuriteo t&otilde;kestamisel tekkinud t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse, kutsehaiguse ning alla 14-aastase haige lapse kodus p&otilde;etamise korral, samuti rasedus- ja s&uuml;nnituspuhkuse v&otilde;i alla 4-aastase lapse lapsendaja puhkuse korral - 100%. </eesti>
<inglise>3) in the case of an accident at work or incapacity for work arising during protection of the interests of the state or society or prevention of a criminal offence, or in the case of occupational disease, nursing a child under 14 years of age who is ill at home, pregnancy and maternity leave, or adoptive parents leave for an adoptive parent of a child under 4 year of age - 100%. </inglise>
<eesti>(04.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 42, 233) </eesti>
<inglise>(04.04.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 42, 233) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Eesti Vabariigi t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduse paragrahvide 62 ja 63 ning avaliku teenistuse seaduse paragrahv 51 alusel ajutiselt t&ouml;&ouml;st v&otilde;i ameti&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisest vabastamise korral makstakse kindlustatule h&uuml;vitist &uuml;he kalendrip&auml;eva kohta 80% &uuml;he kalendrip&auml;eva keskmisest tulust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the case of temporary release from work or from performance of functions on the basis of Articles 62 or 63 of the Republic of Estonia Employment Contracts Act or Article 51 of the Public Service Act, a benefit shall be paid per calendar day to the insured person at a rate of 80 per cent of his or her average income per calendar day. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Eesti Vabariigi t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduse paragrahvide 62 ja 63 alusel t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste ajutise kergendamise v&otilde;i ajutiselt teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le &uuml;leviimise korral ning avaliku teenistuse seaduse paragrahv 51 alusel teenistustingimuste ajutise kergendamise v&otilde;i ajutiselt teisele ametikohale &uuml;leviimise korral makstakse kindlustatule palgavahet niisuguses summas, et palgavahe koos selle aja eest saadava palgaga ei &uuml;letaks kindlustatu keskmist palka. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In the case of temporary easement of working conditions or temporary transfer to another position on the basis of Articles 62 or 63 of the Republic of Estonia Employment Contracts Act or in the case of temporary easement of conditions of service or temporary transfer to another position on the basis of Article 51 of the Public Service Act, the difference in wages shall be paid to the insured person in such an amount that the difference in wages together with the wages received for the corresponding time shall not exceed the average wages of the insured person. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud v&auml;ljastama kindlustatule ja haigekassale h&uuml;vitise ning palgavahe m&auml;&auml;ramiseks ja maksmiseks vajalikud t&otilde;endid, mille vormid kehtestatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 10 6. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Employers are required to provide insured persons and the health insurance funds with the documentation necessary for the grant and payment of benefits and differences in wages, the standard format of which shall be established pursuant to the procedure provided for in subsection 10 (6) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>F&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjale v&auml;ljastab t&otilde;endi maksuamet. </eesti>
<inglise>The Tax Board shall issue the documentation to sole proprietors. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.12.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.12.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10 (5). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10 (5). </inglise>
<eesti>H&uuml;vitise maksmise piirangud </eesti>
<inglise>Restrictions on payment of benefit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kindlustatule ei maksta h&uuml;vitist, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A benefit shall not be paid to an insured person if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) haiguse v&otilde;i vigastuse on p&otilde;hjustanud arsti poolt tuvastatud alkoholi-, narkootikumi- v&otilde;i toksiline joove; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a doctor establishes that the illness or injury is caused by intoxication by alcohol, drugs or toxic substances; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kindlustatu eirab arsti ettekirjutusi, mille t&otilde;ttu paranemine on takistatud; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the insured person disregards the doctor's recommendations, as a result of which his or her recovery is hindered; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kindlustatu ei ilmu t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse ajal arsti poolt m&auml;&auml;ratud vastuv&otilde;tule ilma m&otilde;juva p&otilde;hjuseta, mille kohta arst teeb t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuslehele sellekohase m&auml;rkuse. </eesti>
<inglise>3) during the period of incapacity for work, the insured person fails to appear without good reason at a consultation designated by the doctor, to which effect the doctor shall make a note on the certificate of incapacity for work. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud p&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevate p&auml;evade eest h&uuml;vitist ei maksta; </eesti>
<inglise>The benefit shall not be paid for the days following the day specified; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kindlustatu puudub t&ouml;&ouml;lt k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 4. l&otilde;ike alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>4) the insured person is absent from work on the basis of subsection (4) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kindlustatule ei maksta h&uuml;vitist, kui ajutine t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetus algab: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A benefit shall not be paid to an insured person if temporary incapacity for work commences: </inglise>
<eesti>1) palgata puhkuse ajal; </eesti>
<inglise>1) during holiday without pay; </inglise>
<eesti>2) osaliselt tasustatava puhkuse ajal; </eesti>
<inglise>2) during holiday with partial pay; </inglise>
<eesti>3) lapsehoolduspuhkuse ajal; </eesti>
<inglise>3) during parental leave; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kaitsev&auml;es &otilde;ppekogunemise ajal; </eesti>
<inglise>4) during training exercises in the armed forces; </inglise>
<eesti>5) &otilde;ppepuhkuse ajal; </eesti>
<inglise>5) during study leave; </inglise>
<eesti>6) hoolduslehe alusel p&otilde;hi- ja lisapuhkuse ajal; </eesti>
<inglise>6) on the basis of a certificate for care leave during base or additional holiday; </inglise>
<eesti>7) haigus- ja hoolduslehe alusel rasedus- ja s&uuml;nnituspuhkuse ajal; </eesti>
<inglise>7) on the basis of a certificate for sick leave or care leave during pregnancy and maternity leave; </inglise>
<eesti>8) hoolduslehe alusel kindlustatu ajutise t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>8) on the basis of a certificate for care leave during a period when the insured person is temporarily incapacitated for work. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud juhtudel makstakse h&uuml;vitist p&auml;evast, mil kindlustatu pidi t&ouml;&ouml;le asuma. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In the cases specified in subsection (2) of this section, the benefit shall be paid from the day the insured person should have commenced work. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;andja kehtestatud korras t&ouml;&ouml;andjat informeerides on kindlustatul &otilde;igus t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetusleheta puududa t&ouml;&ouml;lt tervislikel p&otilde;hjustel v&otilde;i kuni 14-aastase lapse hooldamiseks kolm p&auml;eva kalendriaastas, mille eest h&uuml;vitist ei maksta. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An insured person has the right to be absent from work without a certificate of incapacity for work for health reasons or to care for a child of up to 14 years of age for three days during a calendar year for which benefits are not paid, if the employer is informed thereof pursuant to the procedure established by the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Haigekassal on &otilde;igus keelduda h&uuml;vitise maksmisest v&otilde;i n&otilde;uda enammakstud v&otilde;i eba&otilde;igesti makstud h&uuml;vitise v&otilde;i palgavahe summad sisse kindlustatult, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The health insurance fund has the right to refuse to grant a benefit or to collect an overpaid or incorrectly paid benefit or differences in wages from an insured person if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) enammaksmine toimus arvutusvea t&otilde;ttu; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the overpayment was due to a calculation error; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kindlustatu v&otilde;ltsis t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuslehte; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the insured person falsified the certificate of incapacity for work; </inglise>
<eesti>3) haigekassa tuvastab kindlustatu t&ouml;&ouml;tamise t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuslehel m&auml;rgitud t&ouml;&ouml;st vabastamise ajal; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the health insurance fund ascertains that the insured person was working during the time of release from work indicated on the certificate of incapacity for work; </inglise>
<eesti>4) haigekassa tuvastab kindlustatu poolt arsti ettekirjutuste eiramise, mille t&otilde;ttu paranemine on takistatud; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the health insurance fund ascertains that doctor's recommendations were disregarded by the insured person, as a result of which recovery was hindered; </inglise>
<eesti>5) kohus tuvastab, et haiguse v&otilde;i vigastuse p&otilde;hjustas kindlustatu enda s&uuml;&uuml;line k&auml;itumine. </eesti>
<inglise>5) a court establishes that the illness or injury was caused by the wrongful behaviour of the insured person. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Haigekassal on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda sisse: </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The health insurance fund has the right to collect: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&ouml;&ouml;andjalt enammakstud v&otilde;i eba&otilde;igesti makstud h&uuml;vitise v&otilde;i palgavahe summad, kui enammaksmine v&otilde;i eba&otilde;igesti maksmine toimus t&ouml;&ouml;andja poolt esitatud eba&otilde;igete andmete alusel v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andja rikub k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvis 10 (1) s&auml;testatut; </eesti>
<inglise>1) an overpaid or incorrectly paid benefit or differences in wages from the employer if overpayment or incorrect payment was made on the basis of incorrect information submitted by the employer or if the employer violates the provisions of Article 10 (1) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) h&uuml;vitisena makstud ja raviteenuste eest tasutud summad vigastuse tekkimises s&uuml;&uuml;diolevalt isikult; </eesti>
<inglise>2) amounts granted as a benefit and paid for health services from the person guilty of causing the injury; </inglise>
<eesti>3) liiklus&otilde;nnetuse t&otilde;ttu kohustusliku ravikindlustusega h&otilde;lmatud isikule ravikindlustuse eelarve vahenditest makstud h&uuml;vitised ja osutatud raviteenuste maksumuse liikluskindlustusega tegelevalt kindlustusandjalt, kui kohustusliku ravikindlustusega h&otilde;lmatud isikul tekib n&otilde;ude&otilde;igus liikluskindlustusega tegeleva kindlustusandja vastu; </eesti>
<inglise>3) benefits paid to a person covered by compulsory health insurance from the health insurance budgetary funds due to a traffic accident, and the costs of health services rendered, from an insurer engaging in motor third party liability insurance, if the right of claim of the person covered by compulsory health insurance arises against the insurer engaging in motor third party liability insurance; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&ouml;&ouml;andjalt t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetuse v&otilde;i kutsehaiguse tagaj&auml;rjel k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 10 (4) 1. l&otilde;ike punkti 3 alusel 100% ulatuses makstud h&uuml;vitise ja, s&otilde;ltuvalt ravire&zcaron;iimist k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 10 (4) 1. l&otilde;ike punkti 1 v&otilde;i 2 alusel vastavalt 60% v&otilde;i 80% ulatuses arvutatud h&uuml;vitise vahe. </eesti>
<inglise>4) the difference between the benefit paid at a rate of 100 per cent on the basis of clause 10 (4) (1) 3) of this Act as a result of an accident at work or an occupational disease and the benefit calculated at a rate of 60 per cent or 80 per cent, depending on the treatment regime, on the basis of clauses 10 (4) (1) 1) or 2) of this Act, from the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.12.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.12.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 6 punktis 2 nimetatud vigastuse tekitas riik v&otilde;i muu avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja, esitatakse n&otilde;ue riigivastutuse seaduses s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) If the injury specified in clause (6) 2) of this section is caused by the state or another public authority, the claim shall be submitted pursuant to the procedure provided for in the State Liability Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(02.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 47, 260) </eesti>
