<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 2 1. ja 2. l&otilde;ikes loetletud isikute kohustuslik ravikindlustus algab isiku haigekassas arvelev&otilde;tmise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The compulsory health insurance of persons set out in subsections 2 (1) and (2) of this Act shall commence as of the date the persons register with the health insurance fund. </inglise>
<eesti>Sotsiaalmaksu maksja on kohustatud esitama isiku arvelev&otilde;tmiseks etten&auml;htud dokumendid k&uuml;mne kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul, arvates isiku t&ouml;&ouml;le asumise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>The payer of social tax is required to submit the documents prescribed to register a person within ten calendar days after the date on which the person commences work. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.12.98 j&otilde;ust.01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.12.98 entered into force 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 111, 1829) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 2 1. l&otilde;ikes loetletud isikute kohustuslik ravikindlustus kehtib kaks kuud p&auml;rast sotsiaalmaksu maksja poolt kindlustatu eest sotsiaalmaksu tasumist. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The compulsory health insurance of persons set out in subsection 2 (1) of this Act is valid for two months after the payment of social tax by the payer of social tax for the insured person. </inglise>
<eesti>Kindlustatuga v&otilde;rdsustatud isikute kohustuslik ravikindlustus kehtib k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 2 2. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud &otilde;iguslike aluste l&otilde;ppemise p&auml;evani (kaasa arvatud), v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 2 2. l&otilde;ike punktis 3 s&auml;testatud isikud, kelle kohustuslik ravikindlustus kehtib kaks kuud p&auml;rast &otilde;ppeasutuse l&otilde;petamist. </eesti>
<inglise>The compulsory health insurance of persons with equal status to the insured person is valid until the day on which the legal bases provided for in subsection 2 (2) of this Act expire (inclusive), with the exception of persons provided for in clause 2 (2) 3) of this Act whose compulsory health insurance is valid for two months after graduation from an educational institution. </inglise>
